author: aconway
msg: Patches provided by Rajith Attapattu on https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DISPATCH-16
- separately configurable logging levels for each module.
- config stubs for syslog & file based logging (not yet implemented.)
- single configuration section "log", to set defaults use "log : { module:DEFAULT, ... }"
- shorter names for configuration items (print_to_stderr->stderr etc.)
Changed correct but unintuitive bit mask logic: bits in mask were levels NOT selected.
Only log ERROR and above before log system is configured. Avoid annoying INFO log
